caption: A little pricey for rather small portions.  Quality of food is very good though and very tasty.  The service is friendly, but a bit slow.

The food is good if you go to the restaurant,but it taste really bad if you ask them to deliver to your home. Why? The food arrived cold and I waited for a long time. I ordered "El mexicano" burger yesterday and sweet potato fries and the food got here cold. I didn't like that at all.
I like the humberger and fajitas

My daughters and I went for a lovely all girls Valentine's Day brunch! They made the fare look absolutely scrumptious, was artfully plated and even though my be youngest daughter is 8 years old, she was appreciative of it. We all felt so normal again for a little while, it was great. I used to come here for their brunch about once a month when my daughter would be in her ballet class and I was so pleased to be able to come inside for indoor dining and enjoy such a delicious and affordable meal with my DD's. Will be coming in regularly again as long as they remain open! By the way, they have an awesome outdoor dining space on their back deck. I mean it's really nice. Please come in and support our restaurants!
I tried this spot before with my friend and I am addicted since then. I enjoy the good vibes and delightful dishes and beverages. Keep it up.
Food was delicious. Service was even better. He was very attentive and super quick! Very quick backyard outdoor dining. Highly recommend
Local, quality and passion. Delicious food!

I told my friends about this place with my highest recommendations. I visit this restaurant often. I get very good feedback from my friends. The meals are tasty and the stuff is generous and cooperative. always when we go to this place we pass a lovely time.  I warmly recommend this restaurant.

Oh wow!!!. Appetizers are delicious and their steak is to die for. My taste buds dance every time we go there to dine.  The desserts are a must. Staff are polite,  professional and sweet. Bayridge's Hidden Treasure.

One of my favorite restaurants, period. The staff is friendly and engaging and make you feel like family. The food and drinks are always excellent. My partner and I go to this restaurant frequently, and Gourmet Kitchen never disappoints!
I had a terrible experience here. Long wait for food with no explanation and nasty customer service. Food is just okay. Not worth the price or wait. I would suggest to skip this place.

I’ve loved everything I’ve ever ordered here as all the food is delicious but the brunch is TO DIE FOR. And with the healthy options you never leave feeling guilty about your meal. Trust me, order the Eggs Benedict with smoked salmon on Brazilian cheese bread and you’ll never want in another way again. I love how there are so many gluten free and vegan options. I highly recommend.
Good service, good food.

I agree with some of the reviews about the customer service and food being over priced. If this place charges high prices for mediocre food than they should step it up with the customer service. Treat all your customers equally.  EDIT: In response to the owners childish response. Step your game up! Your food isn't good, it's over priced and your customer service sucks! I should know, I experienced dining in your restaurant more than once. Lots of people agree with me and had similar experiences. There are much better places in Bay Ridge.

The customer service is terrible. I waited 2 hours for my food because the waitress never put our order in and blamed it on the kitchen staff. People who came in after us were eating while we sat there with our waters and no food. They are not friendly to people who of African descent. If you are a black person, I don’t recommend coming here.
Lovely service and a great meal!!

I love this place! They give superb food, their menu is rich, The cook in that restaurant is an expert, I like a lot trying all their dishes. The dishes are always fresh, the service towards the customers  is good. I frequently visit this restaurant and I was never discontended. Highly recommended.
Excellent food
Exceptional and fresh food, I like the mood the spot has, and the employees were very kind. Will surely visit here again.

Had an afterrnoon lunch at gourmet fit. Odered the entree:  Zucchini pasta With mushrooms in a light red sauce. This was exceptional!!  My beverage was a glass of organic red spanish wine.  I really enjoyed my tasting experience.

We love to go out. Last night we arrived in this fine restaurant which friends recommended to us. We passed a beautiful time there with superb food and a well-trained team and a great  cuisine. We put this restaurant in our list  and we shall definitely visit again soon. We highly recommend.
Came here for brunch with a friend and the food was delicious. Highly recommend the churros and the passion fruit sangria pitcher. Ask to be seated in the patio area.
Great food, great drinks, great service.  Their truffle fries are really good. A hidden gem on a part of third avenue you typically would avoid.

I’ve been going to Gourmet Fit, and now Gourmet Kitchen for a while now since they first opened almost 5 years ago. Honestly, every experience is excellent, and they have really transformed their menu, service, and found their niche. Me and my girlfriend love going to this place and it is one of the best establishments in Bay Ridge. Their brunch menu is fantastic with loads of options, vegan and non vegan, healthy and not so healthy. Their burgers and steak do not disappoint and their fries are also always crisp, fresh and tasty. Don’t let the facade fool you, the inside is nice and clean and their backyard is well lit and thoughtfully decorated. Definitely check this place out. Also their frozen drinks are refreshing!

first off you would miss this place bc of location and sign doesnt look like a restaurant.Ive passed this area many times and only checked it out bc of restaurant researching in the area saw the reviews and photos. Inside is clean and so is the decor, i got the croquettes they were really good but very small and pricey, they have the slushee machine for the frozen drinks which is good i got the passion fruit sangria and the quinoa salad which was reallly good will go again for the food and cleanliness not too many brazilian restaurants.
Awesome food.

I came here for my first time yesterday because of some of the positive reviews I have seen on Facebook. This place is awesome. The service and food is great. I got the Surf and Turf Burger with the Truffle Fries. Let me tell you...those fries were addicting. I kept dunking them in the house made Chipotle Mayo sauce. I don't think I ate them...I inhaled them. Everything is organic and fresh when it comes out. The place is very clean and the garden in the back is so charming. I will definitely be back!
Food and Service are very good
Good  food  and  attention.

I like to go with friends to this restaurant with my warmest recommendations. I go their often. This recommendation is always successful. The the food there is appetizing and the stuff is welcoming and cooperative. Every time  we go to this place we have a splendid time.  warmly recommended.

Very Comfortable outdoor Garden Patio.  Delicious refreshing drinks, Well cooked yummy Organic Dishes & Great service. The Menu is very limited so choose wisely the food is Delicious.  Definitely, be back soon!!
Plenty of Vegan and gluten free organic options and they cook everything to order!
Food was absolutely delicious......I'm still full actually

Lovely low key space. Food is delicious and beautifully presented. Three of us wwnt for dinner laat night and we sat talking for hours. Although we were the only diners by 9pm we were not rushed. Service was excellent.  My photos do not do the food justice.
Delicious, healthy food in a lovely friendly  atmosphere
Fast services. Atmosphere was good. Great presentation of food.
Churros bomb is delicious. Good food, friendly staff and accommodating to requests

This place makes really good food, and be prepared to spend a bit more $$$. I have dined in and ordered takeout , the waitress is very friendly and the waiting time is great. Great quality and healthy options are available. The Burgers and fries are tasty.
Food is always amazing, friendly and really nice staff and the menu has a lot of options (vegetarian, vegan)!  Highly recommend this place!  One of my favorites ❤️❤️
Burgers are very good!  Plus: carton to go bags📦

I go to this restaurant often! This is the best place to have a bite.  I go to this spot at least once a month. The meals are very tasty, the staff members are friendly and the payment is affordable. I enjoy being in this place over a nice meal.

I think in this price point, you can do better. I had a salmon wrap and my friend had the seared tuna bowl and we were both disappointed about the quality and freshness of the fish. It might be acceptable if you’re paying 7 or 8 bucks for the meal but at 15 to 17 bucks, I expect more.  I don’t think I have much else to add here.
I really enjoy their dishes. I always get awesome service there. The place is well organised and the employees are always super nice. Will visit here again.
Great food and great cuatomer customer service
Love this place. Amazing food, great music, consistently wonderful experience.
Certainly a place worth stopping by, the food is great and well prepared, the cost is reasonable and it is always clean there. Highly recommended.
Would surely recommend trying this spot. Awesome mood, delicious dishes, great customer service. I recommend this place.
This is my go to spot in Bayridge, they have Vegan options, food is good and consistent, I had things delivered also and never had a problem!
The food is good but the place is a little pricey.

Cute little place. Food tasted amazing. You cant tell it's a Brazilian place based on the name of the restaurant. They have some Brazilian music playing in the background, just the right volume so that you can have a conversation. Will definitely be back! My husband ordered the 3 course pre fixe and I had the churrasco. We cleaned our plates :-)  Some recommendations to ownership- I would recommend updating the website so that the menu is clear. When I tried to view it on my phone, it was very pixelated.

Food is good but very pricey for the portion and quality. Staff was friendly but though there were 4 or 5 people working in a half empty restaurant, no one checked on our party for most of the meal, forcing us to go find them near the bar where they were hanging out in order to get more water, utensils, etc.

The food here is to die for!!! The flavors are great and everything's super healthy. The staff is really friendly and patient too! The only reason why I'm giving it 4 stars is because it's really pricey. I guess that's just the price you have to pay for good quality, healthy food.
My husband and I came here for brunch once and it was delicious!
Absolutely delicious!

Stopped here after a walk down to the waterfront and chose the best spot. The wine was great and the food was stellar. I ordered the Peruvian style Cornish hen, which was seasoned to perfection and my partner orded the chicken stroganoff, which was also phenomenal.  I'm looking forward to trying other dishes!
This is a great place to eat.  Every bite of the food is fresh.  This is not fast food, it's wholesome, take your time and eat food.  Highly recommend.

Friendly staff, clean, and welcoming environment. Their menu has a lot of different options, for different times of the day as well. My main problem is that I decided to order a Wagyu Burger, to which I specified Medium cooked. The burger came out well done, with absolutely no pink inside. So $25 for a meal I did not ask for. I would've told the staff about my concern, but I didn't have time nor patience for another burger to be cooked. I understand if it was more medium well than medium, but well done? That's amateur. Additionally, my sweet potato fries came out soggy. They had good flavor but I did not enjoy their texture.
Fantastic food and a lovely ambiance. Excellent whether you want to be health conscious, or indulge - best churros ever!
Extremely fresh with gigantic portions for the price. Everything here was absolutely delicious. I am definitely coming back to try their other bowls.

Good food, nice atmosphere. The service was amazing! But I actually felt bad for our server (she did amazing and it is not her fault) as she was the only one taking the entire restaurant and it looked like she was overwhelmed... maybe the owners could consider adding another person on the floor.
A hidden gem of Bay Ridge that should be discovered by more people.
Gourmet Fit is always a wonderful experience. The staff is incredibly friendly, the food is very healthy and the Brazilian touch to the cuisine gives my fiancee "saudade" for home. 😊❤️🇧🇷
The soups and appetizers were excellent and not too salty. They also had live music the day i went so extra bonus!!
Best Brazilian food at NYC!!!

My fiancé and I found this little gem while dining in Brooklyn heights from a waitress serving our table. She told us about this place and we’ve never looked back. The food is consistently good and fresh. The staff extremely polite and attentive. We really enjoy dining here and it is very clean too. Highly recommended by 2 foodies of Bay Ridge.
Good
Surprise place for really good food. Ask for the Chefs Table Special, No Menu, and just enjoy the variety. Chef Leo and Maria did an amazing job. Group of 6 ate very well.
The food was good, our favorite was the Eggs Benedict.  The "perfect egg sandwich" was a bit dry for my taste but other wise a good experience Also the Churros desert was excellent!! 👌🏽
Food isn't worth the price and the service sucks.
Great food, perfect service, nice brazilian music.... just enjoy!
Great menu. Consistantly good. Super kind staff! Must try the WAFFLE!
I love this place, we are going there weekly. Is it close to our house. Food is fresh, organic and taste delicious. Amazing atmosphere.
Great food and atmosphere Brazilian at its best
Amazing food and service. A must visit.

Fantastic food.. great staff and super fresh food!
Service atmosphere and foods were lovely.  I enjoyed thewood salmon very much.  Tasty and healthy
The Avocado toast is sooo good! And nice atmosphere
Delicious healthy food, nice atmosphere.  My favorite dish is crab&avocado salad. Will definitely go back again to try their brunch menu.
Delicious food and healthy options
Amazing NY Strip Steak (even, when purchased online and delivered)

One of the new restaurants in Northern Bay Ridge on 3rd Avenue. It combines a healthy organic menu along with wine and other beverages. It's a nice welcome to the Bay Ridge area and offers a cozy area to meet for the 18 to 35 crowd moving to the area. Pricing is reasonable and meat is top grade. And it is not open for breakfast but has lunch brunch and dinner menus. After all it is a wine bar. The selection of wine is large and at moderate pricing. Food is definitely above average. While the lighting may not be inviting for intimate meetings, it is a comfortable place for a casual date. Want to come in alone? It's a friendly place that is totally non-intimidating. I hope it finds a following to make this business successful
Perfect brunch and spot on service. The meals are well crafted and decor is fun and vibrant. Would like if the eggs are cage free and a reputable local farm.
Food was delicious and service was excellent.  Would go back again.
Try the salmon burger and the green juice--my favorite meal in the area!
Good quality and delicious food. Friendly staff. One suggestion, change the music to something without such a fast beat. Will make the atmosphere more pleasant.

I went to this place more than I should to try and give them a chance because I eat very clean and always look for healthy options when eating out. I was very disappointed those 5 times I have been there. Their food taste super unhealthy and salty just terrible even their smoothies were very disappointing. Besides the food what makes this place worst is their customer service. They never welcome you or greet you and they always look miserable and ride. You cant ask them any questions both the guy and girl there suck with their rude and cocky attitude. This place is always empty everytime I went I was the only one there and still they never greeted me and if i asked for recommendations or anything about the food they look super bothered. I dont know who the people are that gave them 5 stars but I wouldnt be suprised if they write their own reviews I think most their customers are ordering delivery so they dont deal with the nasty rude attitudes these people have. I will not be returning there. Its super expensive for horrible food and service.
I've only tried delivery, but highly recommend. Initially I thought the wagyu burger was a bit pricey, but then I tasted it. Unreal.

Waitresses were unbelievably nice. Food was delicious. I  can't wait to go back! I had the tuna and my friend had the steak. We also had the calamari as an appetizer. All were delicious. If you are looking for a delicious and healthy meal as well as great Customer service this is the place to go.
Great Healthy food!!
So delicious, good brunch spot

Gourmet Fit is a wonderful zen place with amazing food.  All the food is freshly made.  The Air Fried Quinoa has a scrumptious texture.  The salads are sparkingly crisp & fresh.  The tuna is seared beautifully paired with the avocado mousse & tapioca pearl barley.  Not enough compliments can be said about the chicken quesadilla & vegan wrap. All the dishes are delightful to eat.  One of my favorite places.
Great salads. Humus with eggplant chips amazing! Just about to bite into chicken quesadilla wrap that looks scrumptious.  Great brunch place. Love this place!
Healthy, scrumptious food. The people are extremely friendly and amazing. This place feels like home. Pair your greek chicken or rice bowl with a glass of healthy green detox juice.
Very clean and quiet place.. Nice atmosphere..
Delicious food, EVERYTHING on the menu is great! Organic all the way!
Go Green. Yum
Great atmosphere! This place is adorable! And the food is delicious! Definitely going to make a trip back their!
Wonderful addition to Bay Ridge. Super lovely, casual, clean restaurant. Food/quality/taste is excellent... every time!!
It's a very nice atmosphere. People are really nice and sweet. I tried the grilled chicken and mozzarella sandwich. I don't think I would ever ever find a delicious sandwich like that. Perfection
Amazing..

Tried their baked sweet potato fries, and interestingly they messed it up, it had no taste @all and it felt like they dropped it in a microwave before...    And I'm saying that as someone who bakes sweet potatoes (sometimes make em fries) on a regular basis...
Grass feed beef burger tasted like heaven. Cooked perfectly! Comes with sweet potato fries which are also really good. Definitely coming back.

Outstanding. Highly recommended whether you're looking for a healthy meal or not. The sushi-caliber salmon lightly seared over olive-oil sautéed quinoa with sprouts and peppers was amazing. I will be back here regularly and am telling everyone I know.
Great healthy food and friendly service. I love this place!
Delicious health food! This place is super clean and the food is always fresh. They offer meal plans so you don't have to manage a healthy menu, they do it for you.

We came today to have lunch and was delicios. I had a chicken quesadilha wrap in Mexico once and here was so good that remembered me of it. We also had a Brazil smoothie, fried sweet potatoes, Brazilian cheese rolls (great) and tilapia with rice.  Keep it like this!

This is a hidden gem. A friend of mine dragged me to this "great health food joint"... and his description nailed-it! The food is delicious, fresh and clean. After visiting their website, I noticed they have these amazing meal plan programs and I quickly became and member =)
Love this place! The quality is a step above most places around here. So I really hope more people come here, so they stay in business. The neighborhood needs more places like this!
